# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# <body>
#
# <footer>
#
# --- COMMIT MESSAGE GUIDE ---
# Type: feat, fix, docs, infra, test, chore, refactor
# Scope: deployment, scripts, keda, storage, models, ci, etc.
# Subject: Use imperative mood ("add" not "added"), lowercase, no period, <50 chars
#
# Example:
#   feat(keda): add HTTP interceptor for scale-to-zero
#   infra(k8s): fix GPU resource limits for L4 GPUs
#   docs: expand troubleshooting section in README
#
# TYPES:
#   feat:     New feature or capability
#   fix:      Bug fix or correction
#   docs:     Documentation changes (README, comments)
#   infra:    Infrastructure (Kubernetes manifests, scripts)
#   test:     Test additions or updates
#   chore:    Dependencies, maintenance, no code change
#   refactor: Code restructuring without behavior change
#
# SCOPE (optional but recommended):
#   Use for specific area: deployment, scripts, keda, storage, models, readme, ci, etc.
#
# BREAKING CHANGE: If this breaks compatibility, add:
#   BREAKING CHANGE: description of what broke
#
# Issue reference: If fixes an issue, add:
#   Closes #42
#   Fixes #18
#   Resolves #55
